Temperature dependent AS measurement was further performed to study the defect depth and defect density of state (DOSt). According to the AS and differential capacitance spectra (Additional file 1: Fig. S17), there is a defect signal at the frequency range from 102 to 104 Hz and at the temperature range from 180 to 240 K. The defect depth (Ed) can be calculated by Arrhenius formula (Eq. (6)) [53],6lnfT-2=-EdkB1T+ξ,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
